BILL NO. 265

Republic of the Philippines
Bangsamoro Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao
**BANGSAMORO TRANSITION AUTHORITY PARLIAMENT**
Bangsamoro Government Center, Cotabato City

**SECOND REGULAR SESSION**

**BANGSAMORO AUTONOMY ACT NO. 51**

Begun and held in Cotabato City, on Thursday, the 15th day of September 2022.

**AN ACT FURTHER CONTINUING THE VALIDITY OF THE 2020, 2021, 2022, AND 2023 SPECIAL DEVELOPMENT FUND, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES**

Be it enacted by the Bangsamoro Transition Authority in Parliament assembled:

**SECTION 1.** For the 2020 and 2021 Special Development Fund (SDF), Section 3 of the Bangsamoro Appropriations Act or Bangsamoro Autonomy Act No. 22, as amended, is hereby further amended to read as follows:

> "Section 3. Cash Budgeting System. All appropriations authorized in this Act shall be available for release and obligation for the purpose specified until December 31, 2024, and shall continue to be available for disbursement until fully expended.
> 
> The Ministry of Finance, and Budget and Management is authorized to issue the necessary guidelines for the effective implementation of the cash budgeting system."

**SEC. 2.** For the 2022 SDF, the Bangsamoro Autonomy Act No. 23 is amended to include Section 48-A, as follows:

> "Sec. 48 – A. Special Development Fund Validity. All appropriations under the Special Development Fund shall be available for release and obligation for the purpose specified until December 31, 2024, and shall continue to be available for disbursement until fully expended."

**SEC. 3.** For the 2023 SDF, the Bangsamoro Autonomy Act No. 32 is amended to include Section 50-B, as follows:

> "Section 50 – B. Special Development Fund Validity. All appropriations under the Special Development Fund shall be available for release and obligation for the purpose specified until December 31, 2025, and shall continue to be available for disbursement until fully expended."

**SEC. 4.** All other provisions of the laws governing the above appropriations for the SDF as embodied in Bangsamoro Autonomy Act Nos. 22, 23, and 32 that are not otherwise amended herein shall continue to be in full force and effect unless otherwise further amended by the Parliament.

**SEC. 5.** All laws, decrees, executive issuances, rules, and regulations inconsistent with this Act are hereby repealed or modified accordingly.

**SEC. 6.** This Act shall take effect immediately after its publication in a newspaper of regional circulation in the Bangsamoro Autonomous Region.

(Signed)
**ATTY. PANGALIAN M. BALINDONG**
Speaker

This Act was passed by the Bangsamoro Transition Authority Parliament on Jumada Al-Akhirah 07, 1445/December 20, 2023.

(Signed)
**PROF. RABY B. ANGKAL**
Secretary General

